Class TileState

  • java.lang.Object
    • danaus.TileState
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<TileState>

    public class TileState
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<TileState>
    An instance represents the state of a tile. Not all the information about a tile lives in a TileState object, but the interesting information that may be passed to other objects does.

      • compareTo

        public int compareTo(TileState t)
        Return a negative integer, zero, or a positive integer depending on whether this object is less than, equal to, or greater than obj.

        The comparison is made on the properties in this order:
        (0) location, (1) light, (2) wind, (3) number of aromas, (4) the individual aromas in the lists of aromas, (5) the number of flowers, (6) the individual flowers in the lists of flowers.
        Specified by:
        compareTo in interface java.lang.Comparable<TileState>
